    <h2 class="ui header">Promotional strategy
      <a id="lo3-promo" class="anchor"></a></h2>
    <div class="ui content"><p>The social media promotional strategy was adopted by the selected artist, but had limited success. Which considering the entire project objective was to provide a PR platform means that the event itself would not have generated enough public interest to be considered a success.</p></div>
  </div>
</div>



<div class="ui teal piled segment">
  <div class="active content">
     <h2 class="ui header"> Analysis of data obtained from customer feedback.<a id="lo3-feedback" class="anchor"></a></h2>
     <div class="ui content"><p>The data that can be analysis for this failed event would be that during the heavily politicized time frame of the event, many public bodies/organizations had been be instructed not to formally affiliate them self a political. This would explain the lack of assistance offered and lack of response when trying to communicate with members of staff about arranging the required facilities, equipment or for information. </p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="ui teal piled segment">
  <div class="active content">
    <h2 class="ui header">Recommendations
      <a id="lo3-recommendations" class="anchor"></a>
    </h2>
    <div class="ui content">
      <li> Avoid political subjects: unless formally backed by an member</li>
      <li>Delegate</li>
      <li>have money</li>
      <li>work within you network/bounds</li>
      <li>don't rely one person or group of people more than absolutely necessary, as they need to be replaced</li>
      <li> If I was more flexible when selecting the of host for the event I could have selected one with in suitable bounds of established regional networks. This may have made accessing the required resources would have be a much more simple and responsive process</li>
    </div>
    <div class="ui divider"></div>
    <h3 class="ui header">Other improvements that could ave have been done include:</h3>
    <div class="ui content">
      <li>record a gig not a studio session as it generates more public interest.</li>
      <li>Work as part of a team.</li>
      <li>Use a commercial premises, this adds formalities to the organization of the event along with some other advantages.</li>
      <li>Make sure you have more than enough money to book and transport all the necessary people, facilities and equipment.</li>
      <li>Contacting a touring or local artist or business personality who intendeds to perform a gig or conference at a popular location with in the city which is likely to attract a reasonable amount of attention.</li>
      <li>Provided commercial interest by using a public venue, many venues would see the value in the additional promotional material generated through the event </li>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>



